HEADWORD: Inchoative
<hw>In*cho"a*tive</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inchoativus</ets>, <ets>incohativus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>inchoatif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Expressing or pertaining to a
beginning; inceptive; <as>as, an <ex>inchoative</ex> verb</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Some <xex>inchoative</xex> or imperfect rays.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>W.
Montagu.</au> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>An inchoative verb. See
<er>Inceptive</er>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

